The paper deals with information theory and coding theory, which are closely related to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses random coding ensembles, which are commonly studied in the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also mentions connections to network coding, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses refinements of exponents, which could be related to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper mentions expurgated ensembles, which could be related to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
